sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant App as App code (handler emit, etc.)
    participant Coord as IWorkCoordinator
    participant DB as Postgres
    participant PgB as pgbouncer (transaction-pooling)
    participant Listener as PgWorkNotificationListener
    participant CW as ClaimWorker

    Note over App,DB: Producer side — through pgbouncer
    App->>Coord: CommitHandlerResultAsync(...)
    Coord->>PgB: SQL (pooled connection)
    PgB->>DB: forwarded
    DB->>DB: INSERT INTO wh_outbox/wh_inbox/wh_perspective_events
    DB->>DB: pg_notify('wh_work', 'outbox')<br/>pg_notify('wh_work', 'inbox')<br/>pg_notify('wh_work', 'perspective')
    Note over DB: Notifications buffered until COMMIT;<br/>(channel, payload) pairs deduped
    DB->>DB: COMMIT — at most 3 distinct notifications delivered
    DB-->>PgB: ack
    PgB-->>Coord: ack
    Coord-->>App: result

    Note over Listener,DB: Consumer side — direct connection (1 per pod, bypasses pgbouncer)
    DB-)Listener: NOTIFY wh_work / payload=outbox
    Listener->>Listener: OnSignal(WorkSignalCategory.Outbox)
    Listener-)CW: event handler

    CW->>CW: RequestImmediatePoll()
    Note over CW: Wake semaphore released → next loop iteration runs ClaimWorkAsync

    Note over Listener: Health monitoring
    loop Every ListenKeepaliveInterval (30s default)
        Listener->>DB: SELECT 1
        alt OK
            Listener->>Listener: IsHealthy = true
        else Failure / disconnect
            Listener->>Listener: IsHealthy = false
            Listener-)CW: OnHealthChanged(false)
            CW->>CW: Tighten polling cap (fall back to fast polling)
            Listener->>Listener: Exponential reconnect (1s → 30s cap)
        end
    end
